WEBVTT

00:01.784 --> 00:04.308
[Crickets chirping]

00:04.352 --> 00:11.098
[Swings creaking]

00:14.536 --> 00:16.494
Iris: We don't know
what happened.

00:16.538 --> 00:18.670
It had to have been
someone else.

00:18.714 --> 00:20.846
Silas isn't a murderer.

00:20.890 --> 00:21.804
Felix: Iris...

00:21.847 --> 00:23.153
It's not possible.

00:23.197 --> 00:25.155
Huck: We've seen him
lose it before.

00:25.199 --> 00:27.157
He was drunk.
Blacked out.

00:27.201 --> 00:29.333
He woke up
covered in blood.

00:29.377 --> 00:30.639
Their blood --

00:30.682 --> 00:33.337
He could've stumbled on them
just like us.

00:33.381 --> 00:36.123
He told usthat he doesn't remember,

00:36.166 --> 00:37.602
and I believe him.

00:37.646 --> 00:39.126
All right?
I do.

00:39.169 --> 00:41.911
But we have to look
at the hard facts.

00:41.954 --> 00:44.696
He was angry.He didn't like Percy...

00:44.740 --> 00:47.699
[Breathing shakily]

00:47.743 --> 00:52.095
♪

00:52.139 --> 00:54.010
Tony and Percy
were grifters.

00:54.054 --> 00:55.533
They must've had enemies.

00:55.577 --> 00:57.187
What if someone
that they ripped off

00:57.231 --> 00:58.493
came back for revenge?

00:58.536 --> 01:00.060
Huck: Turned this whole placeupside down.

01:00.103 --> 01:02.932
There's no evidenceanybody else was in here.

01:02.975 --> 01:05.152
Strangers would've taken
their shit.

01:05.195 --> 01:07.893
He was passed out
at the scene,

01:07.937 --> 01:09.286
his wrenchcovered in Tony's blood.

01:09.330 --> 01:10.896
Hope: I don't wanna believe it,
either.

01:10.940 --> 01:12.681
All right? It's the last thingI wanna believe.

01:12.724 --> 01:14.030
But Huck said it.

01:14.074 --> 01:16.119
We have seen Silas
lose it before.

01:16.163 --> 01:17.381
Hope, come on.

01:17.425 --> 01:19.514
We've heard the storiesabout his dad.

01:19.557 --> 01:21.907
You're all acting like
we don't know him.

01:21.951 --> 01:24.084
Silas is our friend.
He has earned our trust.

01:24.127 --> 01:26.216
There has to be
some other explanation.

01:26.260 --> 01:28.175
Wild animals.
Marauders, even. I --

01:28.218 --> 01:29.176
What about Percy?

01:29.219 --> 01:30.655
We never found
his body.

01:30.699 --> 01:32.353
What if he's alive
and he needs our help?

01:32.396 --> 01:33.789
Yes, yes.

01:33.832 --> 01:35.138
He could tell us
what really happened.

01:35.182 --> 01:37.053
We searched, okay?
We did.

01:37.097 --> 01:38.750
For hours.

01:38.794 --> 01:41.188
We found a trail of blood
that stopped at the river.

01:41.231 --> 01:44.234
I mean, even if
he was still alive...

01:44.278 --> 01:46.454
there's no way
he could fight that current.

01:46.497 --> 01:48.673
But why would Silas
attack the people

01:48.717 --> 01:50.110
who were trying
to help us?

01:50.153 --> 01:52.199
I don't know.

01:54.897 --> 01:56.899
I think I know why.

01:56.942 --> 02:01.121
♪

02:01.164 --> 02:02.774
[Gate creaks]

02:12.828 --> 02:14.786
♪

02:14.830 --> 02:16.614
Sorry, kid.

02:26.668 --> 02:30.150
♪

02:30.193 --> 02:32.630
Saw this when we made campthe other night.

02:32.674 --> 02:34.632
♪

02:34.676 --> 02:36.634
Come on.

02:36.678 --> 02:39.811
♪

02:39.855 --> 02:41.987
Wasn't my business.

02:42.031 --> 02:44.207
♪

02:44.251 --> 02:46.122
But it is now.

02:46.166 --> 02:49.908
♪

02:49.952 --> 02:51.649
Elton: So what?

02:51.693 --> 02:53.651
They're drawings.

02:53.695 --> 02:55.479
♪

02:55.523 --> 02:57.133
They're mine.

03:27.207 --> 03:35.302
♪

03:41.308 --> 03:43.266
[Fly buzzing]

03:43.310 --> 03:45.355
[Mouse squeaking]

03:45.399 --> 03:48.532
[Man shouting indistinctly]

03:48.576 --> 03:55.278
♪

03:55.322 --> 03:58.325
[Birds chirping]

04:07.334 --> 04:11.076
[Man coughing]

04:21.130 --> 04:24.046
♪

04:27.092 --> 04:29.051
Dad?

04:29.094 --> 04:32.446
[Breathing heavily]

04:32.489 --> 04:35.275
You.

04:35.318 --> 04:38.147
Man: <i>Wipe that stupid look
off your face and answer me --</i>

04:38.190 --> 04:39.540
<i>Do you want to live
in this shit?</i>

04:39.583 --> 04:41.672
Answer me!
Are you a pig?!

04:41.716 --> 04:42.978
Disrespecting the house

04:43.021 --> 04:44.284
that your grandparents
left for us?!

04:44.327 --> 04:45.589
♪

04:45.633 --> 04:47.112
[Plate shatters]You're gonna make a mess?

04:47.156 --> 04:48.331
♪

04:48.375 --> 04:50.594
[Grunts]

04:50.638 --> 04:52.074
I'll teach you!

04:52.117 --> 04:54.772
I'll teach youto disrespect this house!

04:54.816 --> 04:56.383
[Grunts]

04:56.426 --> 04:58.559
♪

04:58.602 --> 05:00.430
[Glass shatters][Grunts]

05:08.482 --> 05:13.269
♪

05:13.313 --> 05:15.706
[Breathing heavily]

05:15.750 --> 05:17.317
[Coughs]

05:17.360 --> 05:19.754
[Knock on door]

05:19.797 --> 05:24.106
♪

05:24.149 --> 05:26.935
[Crickets chirping]

05:29.764 --> 05:31.766
This is so messed up.

05:33.028 --> 05:35.160
It's just
a couple drawings.

05:35.204 --> 05:37.467
Iris,
you threw these away.

05:37.511 --> 05:39.817
He dug through
our trash...

05:39.861 --> 05:42.342
He was a janitor.
It was his job.

05:42.385 --> 05:43.560
Exactly.

05:43.604 --> 05:45.649
It doesn't have to
mean anything.

05:45.693 --> 05:47.347
It doesn't,
but it might.

05:47.390 --> 05:49.131
He likes you,
Iris.

05:49.174 --> 05:51.481
He was different
with you.

05:51.525 --> 05:53.048
We all saw that.

05:54.397 --> 05:57.400
Maybe he saw thatyou were different with Percy.

05:57.444 --> 06:00.011
No, I wasn't.
He wasn't --

06:00.055 --> 06:02.666
They were in his bag.We should put them back.

06:02.710 --> 06:04.538
Why?

06:05.582 --> 06:07.541
Iris may not have wanted
those drawings,

06:07.584 --> 06:08.672
but Silas did.

06:08.716 --> 06:10.413
All we have

06:10.457 --> 06:12.415
is what we carry
on our backs.

06:12.459 --> 06:14.417
Obviously, Silas thoughtIris' work was important enough

06:14.461 --> 06:15.723
to bring with him.

06:15.766 --> 06:16.985
We have no right
to take that away.

06:22.860 --> 06:24.601
Huck: Book says
we take him to the City.

06:24.645 --> 06:26.168
Have the OPD
arrest him.

06:26.211 --> 06:28.300
Have a trial.

06:28.344 --> 06:29.954
Yeah.

06:29.998 --> 06:32.435
I know.

06:34.002 --> 06:36.134
So you saying
we turn around,

06:36.178 --> 06:38.310
make the long-ass
walk back?

06:38.354 --> 06:41.618
Maybe it's just you
that takes him.

06:41.662 --> 06:43.098
Hmm?

06:43.141 --> 06:44.621
Now that they know
where their dad is,

06:44.665 --> 06:46.667
the girls aren't justgonna turn back.

06:46.710 --> 06:48.146
I-I gotta
keep them safe.

06:48.190 --> 06:49.539
Kid's twice my size.

06:49.583 --> 06:50.975
All he has to do
is sit down

06:51.019 --> 06:53.021
and we ain't
going nowhere.

06:57.373 --> 06:59.810
Then what do we do?

06:59.854 --> 07:00.942
Hmm?

07:00.985 --> 07:04.249
Decision falls on us.

07:04.293 --> 07:08.558
Do we take him with us
or leave him behind?

07:08.602 --> 07:10.734
♪

07:10.778 --> 07:13.563
I do not know.

07:13.607 --> 07:15.913
[Gate creaks]

07:15.957 --> 07:18.916
You shouldn't
come in here.

07:18.960 --> 07:20.657
It's not safe.

07:20.701 --> 07:23.747
♪

07:23.791 --> 07:26.141
I'm not safe.

07:27.490 --> 07:30.493
[Gate creaks]

07:35.237 --> 07:37.500
I disagreewith your hypothesis.

07:39.633 --> 07:41.678
[Sighs]

07:44.812 --> 07:48.729
The only timesI've seen you engage in violence

07:48.772 --> 07:50.557
were in self-defense

07:50.600 --> 07:52.776
or the defense
of someone else.

07:52.820 --> 07:54.952
I hurt you.
Back at the school.

07:54.996 --> 07:56.563
You were defending Iris.

07:56.606 --> 08:00.436
You want me
to be scared of you.

08:00.480 --> 08:02.438
But I'm not.

08:02.482 --> 08:04.048
♪

08:04.092 --> 08:06.747
Because I don't thinkthat you would ever hurt anybody

08:06.790 --> 08:09.097
without just cause.

08:09.140 --> 08:10.315
♪

08:10.359 --> 08:12.492
You said it yourself.

08:12.535 --> 08:16.104
You don't remember
what happened.

08:16.147 --> 08:18.454
Is it so hard
for you to believe

08:18.498 --> 08:19.977
that you might
be innocent?

08:20.021 --> 08:24.199
♪

08:24.242 --> 08:26.593
<i>[Rock music
playing indistinctly]</i>

08:26.636 --> 08:27.985
[Silverware clinking]

08:28.029 --> 08:30.466
So, the guys
at the plant are saying

08:30.510 --> 08:32.947
that we're gonna relax
power rationing

08:32.990 --> 08:34.209
for the holidays.

08:34.252 --> 08:36.254
No more
"two bulb nights."

08:36.298 --> 08:38.779
Maybe there'll beChristmas lights this year.

08:38.822 --> 08:41.956
The kids at school
would love that.

08:41.999 --> 08:44.567
<i>[Music continues]</i>

08:44.611 --> 08:49.964
Silas,
maybe tomorrow...

08:50.007 --> 08:51.661
take you down
to the bazaar,

08:51.705 --> 08:53.968
and you can pick out a gift
for your mom.

08:54.011 --> 08:56.144
[Glass thuds]

08:56.187 --> 08:58.276
<i>[Music continues]</i>

08:58.320 --> 08:59.669
[Sighs]

08:59.713 --> 09:03.194
♪ <i>I want to what I want to</i>♪

09:03.238 --> 09:06.023
<i>[Man singing indistinctly]</i>

09:06.067 --> 09:10.201
♪

09:10.245 --> 09:12.377
[Knock on door]

09:12.421 --> 09:14.858
[Breathing heavily]

09:14.902 --> 09:16.686
♪

09:16.730 --> 09:21.604
[Clock ticking]

09:21.648 --> 09:23.563
[Knock on door]

09:33.616 --> 09:37.402
♪

09:37.446 --> 09:39.056
[Knock on door]

09:39.100 --> 09:42.103
[Ticking continues]

09:44.671 --> 09:46.586
[Knock on door]

09:46.629 --> 09:50.590
♪

09:50.633 --> 09:52.679
Elton: Silas?

09:57.292 --> 10:00.643
If you're not going to
believe in yourself,

10:00.687 --> 10:03.037
I'll have to do it
for you.

10:05.996 --> 10:08.042
But I will need
to find proof

10:08.085 --> 10:09.913
that you
were not involved.

10:09.957 --> 10:12.394
If I can't...

10:12.437 --> 10:15.049
♪

10:15.092 --> 10:17.094
...they're going to
leave you.

10:17.138 --> 10:26.713
♪

10:31.021 --> 10:33.850
[Crickets chirping]

10:40.683 --> 10:42.076
Nope.

10:42.119 --> 10:43.294
Yep.

10:43.338 --> 10:44.687
Felix'll shit twice

10:44.731 --> 10:46.994
if he realizes
you're out here.

10:47.037 --> 10:49.344
I was looking
for Elton.

10:50.214 --> 10:52.739
If you're gonna stand there,
might as well be useful.

11:10.670 --> 11:12.628
[Knocking on door]

11:12.672 --> 11:14.586
[Knocking continues]

11:18.678 --> 11:20.288
[Door creaks]

11:20.331 --> 11:21.506
Silas: Uh...

11:21.550 --> 11:22.725
can I help you?

11:22.769 --> 11:24.509
The walls
are very thin, Silas.

11:24.553 --> 11:26.337
Do you know
what that means?

11:26.381 --> 11:29.123
It means I hear things
I'd rather not hear.

11:29.166 --> 11:31.560
Now, I need to speak
to your mother.

11:31.603 --> 11:33.823
E-Everything's fine.You don't need to --

11:33.867 --> 11:36.260
I'm not leaving
until I see her.

11:36.304 --> 11:39.655
Preferably away
from that piece of human refuse

11:39.699 --> 11:41.309
you call a father.

11:41.352 --> 11:42.832
I don't want to have to go
to the authorities again --

11:42.876 --> 11:44.225
Then don't, please.

11:44.268 --> 11:46.836
My mom's at work.She'll be back later.

11:46.880 --> 11:48.185
It's just me.

11:48.229 --> 11:49.360
Uh...

11:49.404 --> 11:51.711
my dad
doesn't like cops.

11:51.754 --> 11:53.495
I don't want him
to be mad.

11:54.714 --> 11:57.064
Did he hurt you,
Silas?

12:00.067 --> 12:03.026
You can walk out with me
right now.

12:03.070 --> 12:05.725
Wait for your mom
at my place.

12:05.768 --> 12:09.772
I know people that can make sureyou're both safe.

12:09.816 --> 12:12.775
♪

12:12.819 --> 12:14.777
It'll be okay.

12:14.821 --> 12:20.783
♪

12:20.827 --> 12:23.786
Um, I think
you should leave.

12:23.830 --> 12:28.312
♪

12:28.356 --> 12:30.401
If that's
what you want.

12:30.445 --> 12:39.628
♪

12:39.671 --> 12:41.891
[Sighs]

12:51.118 --> 12:52.075
♪

12:52.119 --> 12:55.296
[Footsteps approach]

13:01.955 --> 13:04.044
How you doing?

13:05.132 --> 13:06.437
Yeah.

13:06.481 --> 13:09.223
Stupid question.
I know.

13:10.267 --> 13:12.139
You thirsty?

13:14.141 --> 13:16.447
You need anything from us,
you just holler.

13:16.491 --> 13:17.709
Okay?

13:18.885 --> 13:19.886
Hey.

13:20.974 --> 13:22.889
Okay?

13:31.332 --> 13:33.377
Is Iris okay?

13:37.338 --> 13:39.340
One of her friends
is dead.

13:44.998 --> 13:47.174
What if it wasn't me?

13:53.006 --> 13:54.311
Look...

13:54.355 --> 13:55.660
[Sighs]

13:55.704 --> 13:57.837
I wanna help you,
Silas.

13:57.880 --> 13:59.403
Okay?

13:59.447 --> 14:00.709
But you've got to give me
something to work with here.

14:00.752 --> 14:02.015
I can't remember.

14:02.058 --> 14:03.799
My dad could never
remember anything

14:03.843 --> 14:05.105
when he blacked out,either.

14:05.148 --> 14:07.107
I read your file,
Silas.

14:07.150 --> 14:09.196
You were never convicted.

14:09.239 --> 14:13.330
What happened with your dad
was ruled self-defense.

14:13.374 --> 14:15.550
Was it?

14:17.682 --> 14:19.771
You promised me
a fresh start.

14:20.816 --> 14:26.691
I got one,
probably two people dead.

14:26.735 --> 14:28.215
And on top of that,

14:28.258 --> 14:30.695
I got people inside
that I really care about.

14:30.739 --> 14:31.871
Okay?

14:31.914 --> 14:33.263
And I need
to keep them safe.

14:34.221 --> 14:35.962
What do I do?

14:36.005 --> 14:39.487
Do I trust you
to stay in control?

14:40.531 --> 14:43.665
To not
put everyone else in danger?

14:45.667 --> 14:48.844
I don't
wanna be like this.

14:48.888 --> 14:50.672
Like my dad.

14:52.761 --> 14:54.981
[Sighs]

14:55.024 --> 14:57.679
I know you don't.

15:09.647 --> 15:11.388
[Gate creaks]

15:30.581 --> 15:35.021
♪

15:35.064 --> 15:37.066
[Glass shatters]

15:57.130 --> 16:03.092
♪

16:03.136 --> 16:06.966
[Floorboards creaking]

16:07.009 --> 16:10.491
♪

16:10.534 --> 16:13.581
[Hope grunting]

16:15.148 --> 16:17.063
Huck: Easy...

16:17.106 --> 16:19.021
It's stupid.

16:20.153 --> 16:22.416
I barely knew
the guy.

16:22.459 --> 16:24.984
And he tried to stealall of our stuff.

16:25.027 --> 16:26.768
[Sighs]

16:26.811 --> 16:29.466
Kind of a dick,
actually.

16:29.510 --> 16:30.946
So...

16:30.990 --> 16:33.122
he was all right.

16:33.166 --> 16:34.471
Yeah.

16:34.515 --> 16:38.649
He was a mixed bag,
like everybody.

16:38.693 --> 16:40.260
Even Silas.

16:40.303 --> 16:42.740
If you're trying to get meto forgive and forget...

16:42.784 --> 16:44.133
[Scoffs]
Not saying that.

16:44.177 --> 16:45.482
Feel how
you wanna feel.

16:45.526 --> 16:47.615
Be sad.
Be pissed.

16:47.658 --> 16:50.313
Just keep
asking yourself

16:50.357 --> 16:53.012
how to serve
the greater good.

16:53.055 --> 16:55.536
That's how
you stay focused.

16:56.711 --> 16:58.626
You've got
the wrong sister.

16:58.669 --> 17:01.063
Iris has always beenthe good one.

17:01.107 --> 17:03.152
I'm talking
the greater good.

17:03.196 --> 17:06.634
Doesn't always have to be about
right or wrong.

17:06.677 --> 17:09.854
It's about doing what's best
for everybody,

17:09.898 --> 17:11.856
even when you know
it's gonna hurt.

17:11.900 --> 17:15.556
You all want to get to
the C.R.'s research place?

17:15.599 --> 17:16.992
Help your Dad?

17:17.036 --> 17:20.517
Every choice has to be about
making it there.

17:20.561 --> 17:23.955
♪

17:23.999 --> 17:28.438
Sometimes what's painful
in the moment...

17:28.482 --> 17:32.442
is what gets you
where you need to go.

17:32.486 --> 17:35.793
[Shovel clatters]

17:35.837 --> 17:37.795
♪

17:37.839 --> 17:40.798
Deep enough.

17:44.846 --> 17:47.022
[Crickets chirping]

17:47.066 --> 17:49.546
[Door opens, closes]

17:49.590 --> 17:52.027
[Footsteps approach]

17:52.071 --> 17:53.811
Hey.

17:53.855 --> 17:57.163
Any progress?

17:58.338 --> 18:00.296
I thought
breaking this code

18:00.340 --> 18:01.732
would be
a good distraction,

18:01.776 --> 18:05.693
but instead it's justreminding me of how...

18:05.736 --> 18:07.651
nothing makes sense.

18:09.610 --> 18:12.178
We buried Tony.

18:12.221 --> 18:15.659
And we left markers
for him and Percy.

18:19.620 --> 18:21.883
Even with everything...

18:21.926 --> 18:24.059
the blackout,
the blood...

18:24.103 --> 18:26.235
I just...

18:26.279 --> 18:29.412
I still have this feelingSilas didn't do it.

18:29.456 --> 18:31.849
Never know
what someone's capable of.

18:33.155 --> 18:34.852
You didn't know
what I was.

18:34.896 --> 18:37.246
One mistakedoesn't make you a bad person.

18:37.290 --> 18:39.770
Silas didn't just
make one mistake.

18:39.814 --> 18:41.294
How many chances
do we get?

18:41.337 --> 18:43.861
Hope...
We know
where Dad is now.

18:43.905 --> 18:47.082
We are so close.

18:47.126 --> 18:50.694
We can't let anyone
stand in the way of that.

18:54.133 --> 18:56.570
I wanna believe him.

18:56.613 --> 18:58.572
♪

18:58.615 --> 19:00.313
Because if he did it,

19:00.356 --> 19:02.750
I should've
seen it coming.

19:02.793 --> 19:04.055
I should've known.

19:04.099 --> 19:06.580
Not if
he didn't want you to see.

19:06.623 --> 19:09.104
♪

19:09.148 --> 19:11.150
Maybe he thought
he was protecting you.

19:11.193 --> 19:12.412
No, that would only
make it worse.

19:12.455 --> 19:13.630
How?

19:13.674 --> 19:15.980
It'd meanhe let me live in a lie.

19:26.034 --> 19:28.297
♪

19:28.341 --> 19:30.647
[Glass crunches]

19:30.691 --> 19:34.608
[Floorboards creaking]

19:44.183 --> 19:46.794
Dad?

19:46.837 --> 19:48.796
You in there?

19:58.849 --> 20:03.898
♪

20:08.685 --> 20:10.774
[Clattering in distance]

20:13.777 --> 20:16.824
[Clattering continues]

20:23.570 --> 20:28.879
♪

20:28.923 --> 20:31.055
Dad?

20:31.099 --> 20:32.535
♪

20:32.579 --> 20:34.233
You shouldn't be out thereby yourself.

20:34.276 --> 20:35.495
Okay,the last thing we need

20:35.538 --> 20:37.236
is somebody else
getting killed.

20:37.279 --> 20:38.541
Where were you?

20:38.585 --> 20:41.065
Found him
out by the river.

20:41.109 --> 20:44.112
Do me a favor --
keep an eye on him.

20:44.155 --> 20:47.333
[Footsteps depart]

20:47.376 --> 20:50.336
I followed
Percy's trail,

20:50.379 --> 20:53.252
looking for evidence
to exonerate Silas.

20:53.295 --> 20:55.297
You find any?

20:55.341 --> 20:57.473
I don't know forensics.

20:57.517 --> 20:59.954
And it's dark,
so no.

21:00.955 --> 21:02.826
Why are you fighting so hardfor a lost cause?

21:02.870 --> 21:04.132
'Cause it isn't.

21:04.175 --> 21:05.612
Look, we don't know
what happened.

21:05.655 --> 21:07.178
The only fact
I know

21:07.222 --> 21:09.703
is that I haven't had a family
in a long time.

21:09.746 --> 21:10.921
But I have one now.

21:11.966 --> 21:14.316
Even if Silas is guilty,
he deserves our help.

21:14.360 --> 21:15.709
That's what family does.

21:15.752 --> 21:17.537
So you'd just
forgive him?

21:18.625 --> 21:20.061
Let himget away with murder?

21:22.193 --> 21:24.979
I don't think it's something
you get away with.

21:25.022 --> 21:27.286
You still have to live with
what you've done.

21:30.376 --> 21:32.943
We have to focuson the greater good.

21:32.987 --> 21:34.945
What's best
for everyone.

21:34.989 --> 21:37.383
What's best
is for us to stay together.

21:38.471 --> 21:40.777
♪

21:40.821 --> 21:42.997
Dad?

21:43.040 --> 21:46.130
[Stairs creaking]

22:16.204 --> 22:21.470
♪

22:21.514 --> 22:23.646
Didn't mean to hurt you.

22:23.690 --> 22:25.735
Just wanted you to stop.

22:25.779 --> 22:28.303
Please.

22:28.347 --> 22:31.654
[Growling]

22:51.718 --> 22:56.287
♪

22:56.331 --> 22:58.464
[Lamp shatters]

22:58.507 --> 23:01.510
[Growling continues]

23:11.390 --> 23:13.348
♪

23:13.392 --> 23:16.351
[Growling, pounding on door]

23:36.415 --> 23:44.161
♪

23:47.991 --> 23:50.777
[Growling continues]

23:50.820 --> 23:54.258
<i>[Heavy-metal music
playing loudly]</i>

23:54.302 --> 23:56.478
♪

23:56.522 --> 23:58.698
Man: Silas.

23:58.741 --> 24:01.875
Silas: Yeah?

24:01.918 --> 24:04.094
Lie down.

24:04.138 --> 24:06.096
♪

24:06.140 --> 24:08.272
What,
you don't trust me?

24:18.326 --> 24:25.115
♪

24:25.159 --> 24:26.900
Close your eyes.

24:26.943 --> 24:30.947
Go on.
♪ <i>You need</i>♪

24:30.991 --> 24:32.906
You wanna hearwhat a real concert sounded like

24:32.949 --> 24:35.474
before everything
went to shit?

24:35.517 --> 24:36.605
♪ <i>You take</i>♪

24:36.649 --> 24:38.302
♪ <i>What I make</i>♪

24:38.346 --> 24:42.263
♪ <i>Or you're living a lie</i>♪

24:42.306 --> 24:45.788
♪ <i>We want to feel it</i>♪

24:45.832 --> 24:49.139
♪

24:49.183 --> 24:51.446
♪ <i>Feel it now</i>♪

24:51.490 --> 24:52.882
♪ <i>Oh, oh</i>♪

24:52.926 --> 24:55.276
You gotta imagine
thousands of voices,

24:55.319 --> 24:57.800
shouting the words
all around you.

24:57.844 --> 25:00.934
The bass
shaking the sky.

25:00.977 --> 25:03.066
When I saw AC/DC
in '88,

25:03.110 --> 25:06.461
they practically cracked
the arena in half.

25:06.505 --> 25:08.376
[Both laugh]

25:08.419 --> 25:12.554
This is what music
should be like.

25:12.598 --> 25:16.036
You should feel it
in your entire body.

25:16.079 --> 25:18.299
Feel that?

25:18.342 --> 25:19.953
Yeah.

25:19.996 --> 25:21.911
I feel it.

25:24.784 --> 25:27.177
♪ <i>Light the night</i>♪

25:27.221 --> 25:28.570
Whoo!

25:28.614 --> 25:31.834
Whoo-hoo-hoo-hooo!

25:31.878 --> 25:34.968
♪ <i>In the days of long ago</i>♪

25:35.011 --> 25:37.797
♪ <i>A not too distant time</i>♪

25:37.840 --> 25:42.149
♪ <i>You fought for freedom,
and they paid the price♪</i>

25:42.192 --> 25:45.195
♪ <i>They won the battle</i>♪

25:55.249 --> 25:57.817
♪

25:57.860 --> 26:02.343
[Thudding]

26:02.386 --> 26:04.040
[Growling continues]

26:04.084 --> 26:06.869
♪

26:06.913 --> 26:09.350
♪ <i>They won the battle</i>♪

26:09.393 --> 26:11.613
♪ <i>The right to be free</i>♪

26:11.657 --> 26:13.876
[Volume decreases]

26:13.920 --> 26:18.446
♪

26:18.489 --> 26:23.451
♪ <i>Returned by our hand</i>♪

26:23.494 --> 26:24.626
♪ <i>Yeah</i>♪

26:24.670 --> 26:28.935
♪ <i>Proclaim for all to see</i>♪

26:28.978 --> 26:30.719
♪ <i>The crosses made</i>♪

26:30.763 --> 26:33.809
[Crickets chirping]

26:39.772 --> 26:43.776
♪

26:43.819 --> 26:47.257
[Walker growling]

26:56.963 --> 27:01.010
♪

27:01.054 --> 27:03.622
[Sighs]

27:03.665 --> 27:11.630
♪

27:11.673 --> 27:14.633
[Fence rattling]

27:24.686 --> 27:26.253
♪

27:26.296 --> 27:29.473
<i>[Heavy-metal music playing]</i>

27:29.517 --> 27:32.738
[Music stops]

27:40.354 --> 27:44.010
[Floorboards creak]

27:48.710 --> 27:50.886
[Clattering in distance]

27:53.846 --> 27:56.326
Woman: Silas?

27:56.370 --> 27:58.111
Silas?

27:58.154 --> 27:59.808
[Screaming]

27:59.852 --> 28:01.636
Mom!
No!

28:01.680 --> 28:02.637
[Screams]

28:02.681 --> 28:04.726
[Growling]

28:04.770 --> 28:07.816
Mom,
get out of the house!

28:07.860 --> 28:09.513
[Growling continues]

28:09.557 --> 28:12.516
[Fence rattling]

28:12.560 --> 28:17.957
♪

28:18.000 --> 28:19.001
[Screaming]

28:19.045 --> 28:21.134
Mom,
get out of the house!

28:21.177 --> 28:24.354
[Growling]

28:34.408 --> 28:35.844
♪

28:35.888 --> 28:38.847
[Grunts]

28:58.911 --> 28:59.868
♪

28:59.912 --> 29:02.392
[Squelching]

29:02.436 --> 29:05.787
♪

29:05.831 --> 29:08.877
[Crying]

29:08.921 --> 29:18.800
♪

29:18.844 --> 29:20.846
[Crying]

29:20.889 --> 29:23.196
♪

29:23.239 --> 29:26.199
[Growling continues]

29:26.242 --> 29:31.639
♪

29:31.682 --> 29:33.815
[Sighs]

29:33.859 --> 29:36.818
Stay back.

29:36.862 --> 29:38.733
[Crying]

29:38.777 --> 29:40.648
[Growling continues]

29:42.258 --> 29:43.869
Stay back.

29:43.912 --> 29:47.089
[Growling continues]

29:57.143 --> 30:07.196
♪

30:09.895 --> 30:12.027
[Sighs]

30:19.165 --> 30:26.520
♪

30:26.563 --> 30:28.478
What the hell?

30:28.522 --> 30:30.829
♪

30:30.872 --> 30:32.831
You should've yelled.I-I -- Why didn't you?

30:32.874 --> 30:35.834
I almost...

30:35.877 --> 30:37.836
♪

30:37.879 --> 30:40.447
I don't know
if you meant to,

30:40.490 --> 30:43.406
but I thinkyou probably did it.

30:44.712 --> 30:46.453
I'm sorry,but it's just what I think.

30:48.150 --> 30:50.239
Why'd you save me?

30:50.283 --> 30:52.154
[Scoffs]

30:52.198 --> 30:54.504
Enough people have died.

31:04.558 --> 31:10.956
♪

31:15.047 --> 31:17.832
[Crickets chirping]

31:26.797 --> 31:29.844
[Footsteps depart]

31:37.896 --> 31:40.333
You asleep?

31:40.376 --> 31:42.683
[Sniffles]

31:44.032 --> 31:47.122
I don't think any of uscan sleep right now.

31:48.167 --> 31:50.256
Every time
I close my eyes...

31:55.391 --> 31:56.915
I keep thinking about

31:56.958 --> 32:00.266
something Hope used to saywhen we were kids.

32:01.702 --> 32:05.532
That the sky is full of starsthat have already died.

32:06.576 --> 32:08.796
Empty stars.

32:08.839 --> 32:13.235
Their light carrying on acrossmillions of miles of space

32:13.279 --> 32:14.933
after they're gone.

32:14.976 --> 32:19.415
It's a graveyard
up there.

32:19.459 --> 32:24.072
Actually, stars visible
to the human eye

32:24.116 --> 32:26.727
are mostly a couple of hundred
light-years away.

32:26.770 --> 32:28.207
We'd be able to tell

32:28.250 --> 32:31.079
if they were in
the early stages of death.

32:31.123 --> 32:32.646
So...

32:32.689 --> 32:36.041
The stars that you're looking atup there...

32:36.084 --> 32:38.782
they're very much alive.

32:38.826 --> 32:41.960
I hope
that makes you feel better.

32:45.180 --> 32:47.139
It does.

32:47.182 --> 32:49.924
A little.

32:51.534 --> 32:54.798
How are you doing
with everything?

32:54.842 --> 32:55.843
Oh.

32:55.886 --> 32:58.063
I've been thinking, too.

32:58.106 --> 33:02.458
I've been operating under
a false assumption.

33:02.502 --> 33:04.808
I mean,
there are no laws out here,

33:04.852 --> 33:07.637
and as such,
nothing specifically

33:07.681 --> 33:10.510
empowers the adults
to decide Silas' fate.

33:11.902 --> 33:14.688
I mean, you're the closest thingto a leader we have.

33:15.863 --> 33:18.735
You should have equal say
in what happens to Silas.

33:18.779 --> 33:21.129
And so should I.

33:21.173 --> 33:23.697
And -- And Hope.

33:23.740 --> 33:25.307
Elton...

33:25.351 --> 33:29.659
This isn't justsome problem to solve.

33:29.703 --> 33:32.967
If you refuse
to exile Silas,

33:33.011 --> 33:34.490
then all we'd need

33:34.534 --> 33:36.623
is one more vote
in our favor.

33:37.885 --> 33:41.019
Then we'd have the majority,
and Silas can stay.

33:41.062 --> 33:43.282
Hope won't...

33:43.325 --> 33:46.285
You think Huck...?

33:46.328 --> 33:48.591
Not Huck.

33:53.553 --> 33:55.598
He doesn't want
to leave anybody.

33:55.642 --> 33:57.513
If we present
a united front,

33:57.557 --> 33:59.994
I-I think
he'll back us.

34:01.213 --> 34:03.563
It's up to you.

34:03.606 --> 34:06.653
[Birds chirping]

34:26.151 --> 34:28.240
Why'd you keep them?

34:31.852 --> 34:34.028
They were too beautiful
to throw away.

34:40.165 --> 34:42.515
Tell meyou didn't kill anyone.

34:45.039 --> 34:47.955
If you say it,
I'll believe you.

34:47.998 --> 34:51.437
[Voice breaking] I told you oncewe wouldn't leave you.

34:51.480 --> 34:53.700
Help me keep my promise,Silas.

34:58.270 --> 35:00.533
Hope: Iris?

35:05.277 --> 35:07.496
Wait.

35:11.805 --> 35:13.415
I got free last night.

35:13.459 --> 35:15.635
I wanted
to talk to you.

35:19.639 --> 35:22.598
I didn't want you
to see me like this.

35:22.642 --> 35:24.165
Silas --

35:24.209 --> 35:26.428
I wish I could tell you
what you need to hear.

35:26.472 --> 35:28.474
♪

35:28.517 --> 35:30.998
I don't remember much.

35:31.041 --> 35:33.087
Just being angry.

35:33.131 --> 35:34.132
♪

35:34.175 --> 35:36.308
It's happened before.

35:36.351 --> 35:39.398
I thinkthere's something wrong with me.

35:39.441 --> 35:42.140
No, Silas...

35:42.183 --> 35:43.619
♪

35:43.663 --> 35:45.578
Thank you
for believing in me.

35:45.621 --> 35:48.276
Wanting me
to be a hero.

35:48.320 --> 35:51.018
I wanted that, too.

35:51.061 --> 35:53.325
I killed my dad.

35:53.368 --> 35:56.632
I killed Percy and Tony.

35:56.676 --> 35:58.634
I'm a killer.

35:58.678 --> 36:01.159
♪

36:01.202 --> 36:03.770
I don't want to cause you
any more problems,

36:03.813 --> 36:05.598
so I won't.

36:05.641 --> 36:08.122
I'm sorry you met me.

36:08.166 --> 36:11.299
But I'm glad
I got to know you, Iris.

36:11.343 --> 36:19.438
♪

36:19.481 --> 36:21.788
I'll never forget you.

36:41.851 --> 36:45.159
♪

36:45.203 --> 36:47.466
What happened?

36:47.509 --> 36:51.165
♪

36:51.209 --> 36:53.211
He's gone.

37:03.264 --> 37:09.923
♪

37:09.966 --> 37:13.840
Think he'll
change his mind?

37:13.883 --> 37:16.234
Come back for us?

37:16.277 --> 37:17.757
♪

37:17.800 --> 37:19.933
I don't.

37:19.976 --> 37:24.067
No, all he wanted
was a fresh start.

37:24.111 --> 37:26.896
Maybe now
he'll finally get one.

37:26.940 --> 37:28.246
Yeah.

37:28.289 --> 37:29.943
[Footsteps approach]

37:29.986 --> 37:32.032
Hope:Are we leaving already?

37:42.085 --> 37:46.612
I have come toa very difficult decision.

37:51.138 --> 37:53.227
I'm leaving
to join Silas.

37:53.271 --> 37:55.316
His odds of survivalincrease dramatically

37:55.360 --> 37:57.449
with suppliesand somebody watching his back.

37:57.492 --> 37:59.320
You can't.
That's crazy.

37:59.364 --> 38:00.539
If I don't
go after him,

38:00.582 --> 38:02.410
Silas will spendthe rest of his life

38:02.454 --> 38:05.326
thinking thatnobody believes in him.

38:06.501 --> 38:08.373
He'll spend the rest of his life
believing a lie.

38:08.416 --> 38:10.113
I just...

38:10.157 --> 38:12.290
I can't
let that happen.

38:15.467 --> 38:17.773
You'll give my best
to the others?

38:17.817 --> 38:20.733
It's going to be too hardto say goodbye, so...

38:20.776 --> 38:22.300
I-I'd rather not.

38:22.343 --> 38:23.953
You're serious.

38:23.997 --> 38:26.608
You're really leaving.

38:26.652 --> 38:28.784
We could never
see you again.

38:28.828 --> 38:30.133
What about our family?

38:30.177 --> 38:32.484
Silas is family, too.

38:42.668 --> 38:46.236
Everything happensthe way it's supposed to.

38:48.195 --> 38:51.546
And I thinkI'm supposed to find him.

38:52.591 --> 38:54.680
And then I thinkI'm supposed to find

38:54.723 --> 38:56.812
my mother
and my sister, too.

38:56.856 --> 38:59.380
Elton --
Look,
I-I thought it was crazy,

38:59.424 --> 39:00.555
but you were right.

39:00.599 --> 39:01.991
They could still
be out there.

39:02.035 --> 39:03.384
It's just like my father'striceratops horn.

39:03.428 --> 39:05.865
If I could --But what if they're not?

39:05.908 --> 39:08.433
Not what?

39:08.476 --> 39:10.260
[Sniffles]

39:10.304 --> 39:13.089
I lied to you,
Elton.

39:13.133 --> 39:16.092
I thought I was protecting you
from the truth,

39:16.136 --> 39:17.398
but I made it worse.

39:17.442 --> 39:19.095
I don't understand.

39:19.139 --> 39:21.794
You can't keep looking
for someone that's not there.

39:21.837 --> 39:24.100
♪

39:24.144 --> 39:26.364
I can't
let you do that.

39:26.407 --> 39:29.802
I'm so sorry.

39:29.845 --> 39:32.631
[Sniffles]

39:32.674 --> 39:34.937
♪

39:34.981 --> 39:36.765
You forgave Silas.

39:36.809 --> 39:39.768
Maybe one day,
you'll forgive me, too.

39:49.822 --> 39:54.087
♪

39:54.130 --> 39:58.831
The Night the Sky Fell,
I was with my mom.

39:58.874 --> 40:02.051
There was a woman
with a gun.

40:02.095 --> 40:03.531
[Sniffles]
I didn't know it

40:03.575 --> 40:04.880
until I saw the picture
in the book, but...

40:04.924 --> 40:08.797
it was your mom.

40:08.841 --> 40:11.800
And she was scared.

40:11.844 --> 40:13.672
My mom tried
to calm her down,

40:13.715 --> 40:15.108
and I jumped
between them,

40:15.151 --> 40:17.980
and the gun went off
and my mom...

40:18.024 --> 40:19.329
she died.

40:19.373 --> 40:22.594
I don't know
if your mom meant to do it,

40:22.637 --> 40:26.249
but she dropped the gun,
and I picked it up.

40:26.293 --> 40:28.600
I didn't know
what to do,

40:28.643 --> 40:31.254
so I pointed it at her
and it went off in my hand.

40:31.298 --> 40:33.256
♪

40:33.300 --> 40:36.738
[Walker growling]

40:36.782 --> 40:39.262
♪

40:39.306 --> 40:43.397
[Breathing heavily]

41:03.461 --> 41:11.251
♪

41:11.294 --> 41:13.471
[Sniffles]

41:13.514 --> 41:23.393
♪

41:23.437 --> 41:26.440
[Walker growling]

41:26.484 --> 41:35.144
♪

41:35.188 --> 41:38.321
[Thud, growling stops]

41:38.365 --> 41:40.585
[Wood clatters]

42:20.407 --> 42:23.845
♪

42:23.889 --> 42:26.935
[Watch ticking]

42:32.375 --> 42:34.421
Man: <i>Lieutenant Colonel,
we have eyes.</i>

42:37.555 --> 42:40.122
Good.
Bring her in.

42:40.166 --> 42:43.604
She's late,
but she made it.

42:43.648 --> 42:44.823
She did.

42:44.866 --> 42:46.999
This far at least.

42:47.042 --> 42:48.522
It'll only get harder

42:48.566 --> 42:50.524
on this sideof the Mississippi River.

42:50.568 --> 42:52.570
She's aware.
So am I.

42:53.701 --> 42:55.311
With respect,
I just wonder

42:55.355 --> 42:58.227
if there isn'tan easier way to --There isn't.

42:58.271 --> 42:59.751
We know there isn't

42:59.794 --> 43:01.753
because she's the one
who was on the ground,

43:01.796 --> 43:03.755
watching and listening

43:03.798 --> 43:06.453
and doing the very hard thing
of becoming someone else

43:06.496 --> 43:08.411
to find out
there isn't.

43:08.455 --> 43:10.457
She knows
it's dangerous.

43:10.500 --> 43:12.415
She knows she could die.
They both could.

43:12.459 --> 43:17.377
She's out here
risking everything

43:17.420 --> 43:20.206
because there's no
easier way.

43:23.339 --> 43:25.428
[Door creaks]

43:25.472 --> 43:28.388
[Footsteps approach]

43:36.309 --> 43:37.658
[Sighs]

43:37.702 --> 43:39.747
[Door closes]

43:39.791 --> 43:41.227
♪

43:41.270 --> 43:43.969
I was only able to get awayfor about 48 hours.

43:44.012 --> 43:46.101
I'm not back soon,they'll come looking.

43:46.145 --> 43:50.497
♪

43:50.540 --> 43:52.499
What about the asset?

43:52.542 --> 43:54.544
The asset's safe.

43:54.588 --> 43:55.763
And you?

43:55.807 --> 43:59.724
I'm fine, yeah.

43:59.767 --> 44:00.942
Good.

44:00.986 --> 44:03.510
Clean up,
we'll debrief.

44:03.553 --> 44:04.946
And take this.

44:04.990 --> 44:07.253
[Watch ticking]

44:07.296 --> 44:09.603
Is this...

44:09.647 --> 44:11.300
Dad's?

44:11.344 --> 44:13.955
♪

44:13.999 --> 44:15.957
So next time
you won't be late.

44:16.001 --> 44:23.138
♪

44:23.182 --> 44:25.401
[Sighs]

44:49.295 --> 44:58.217
♪
